OL,3,CWhy Wes Streeting is abolishing NHS
OL,4,CEngland
OL,6,FAnd given that the previous Tory
OL,7,Fadministration banged on about wanting
OL,8,Fto abolish fat and waste in the public
OL,9,Fsector, NHS England therefore looks a
OL,10,Frational place to start.
OL,12,FPossibly Johnson, Truss and Sunak were
OL,13,Fscared of being accused of squeezing
OL,14,Fthe country's beloved health service,
OL,15,Fagainst a background of their party
OL,16,Fnot being widely trusted on its
OL,17,Fstewardship of it. But sacking
OL,18,F"managers" - as opposed to nurses and
OL,19,Fdoctors - is rarely unpopular.
